=?utf-8?Q?Fran=C3=A7ois-Paul_Servant?=  on dev@jena.apache.org replies:
the proposal to use a parse method allows to change current code from:

```
        ReaderRIOT reader =3D RDFDataMgr.createReader(Lang.JSONLD);
        try (InputStream in =3D new =
ByteArrayInputStream(jsonld.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))) {
            reader.read(in, null, null, =
StreamRDFLib.dataset(ds.asDatasetGraph()), jenaCtx);
        }
```

to:

```
        try (InputStream in =3D new =
ByteArrayInputStream(jsonld.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))) {
            RDFDataMgr.parse(StreamRDFLib.dataset(ds.asDatasetGraph()), =
in, null, Lang.JSONLD, jenaCtx);
        }
```

That=E2=80=99s indeed one line instead of 2, and one param less in the =
method used (ContentType, here set to null).
Simpler indeed.=20
